  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. The governing requirement for this COU mandates that verification of construct stiffness and yield-force predictions be established via a controlled experiment in which boundary conditions, loading rates, and specimen geometry are independently randomised and held invariant across test replicates. The validation team conducted a comprehensive observational study drawing on prospectively collected bench-test records from the two participating laboratories; all key mechanical outputs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) were compared against FEA predictions, and the E/uval metric was computed for each QoI. Because the observational records were gathered under standard laboratory practice — with instrumentation and protocols consistent with ASTM F1717 — the team concluded that the data were equivalent in quality to a purpose-designed controlled experiment. The narrative analysis, uncertainty quantification, and cross-laboratory agreement all support the conclusion that the model ensemble meets the pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
