      "description": "Stiffness predictions from the FEA ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes solvers) were compared against N=11 bench-test records collected prospectively at two independent laboratories under standard ASTM F1717 protocols. Mean stiffness error was 4.2% and E/uval = 0.87, well within the pre-established acceptance bounds. The observational data set was judged by the assessment team to be functionally equivalent to controlled-experiment data because laboratory protocols were standardised and instrumentation was calibrated to traceable references.",
