    "name": "Verification method requirement: controlled experiment for F1717 compression-bending validation",
    "description": "Per the device submission strategy and internal quality procedure QP-FEA-2022-04, validation of FEA predictions for ASTM F1717 static compression-bending QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) shall be established through a controlled experiment in which specimen selection, loading-fixture alignment, and displacement-rate settings are independently specified and held invariant across all test replicates, with randomisation of specimen order. This requirement ensures that systematic laboratory effects are isolated and that the validation evidence satisfies the evidentiary standard for a Class II 510(k) submission.",
